<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900907-0168</DOCNO><DOCID>900907-0168.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   The Language Barrier</HL><DATE>09/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15</SO><CO>   CANDA</CO><LP>   As Premier Robert Bourassa points out (Americas column,op-ed page, Aug. 17), currently high interest rates are nothelping small business in Quebec. But another big factor noteven mentioned is the province's continuing xenophobicintolerance of the English language. The welcome mat says&quot;bienvenue&quot; but something's getting lost in the translation.   Gary A. Lyon</LP><TEXT>   Westfield, N.J.</TEXT></DOC>